msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:5
msgid "Handling Software Installation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:7
msgid ""
"Installing software on laptops has gotten a lot better over the years, "
"but it can still be a huge challenge at the start of a workshop.  Here "
"are some suggestions for making the process go as smoothly as "
"possible.Software installation can be frustrating, but in the end, it "
"almost always gets done.  Be positive, and when it finally works, you can"
" feel proud."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:10
msgid "What you can do in advance:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:12
msgid ""
"Plan for installation help at the start of both workshop days.  Put it on"
" the schedule and make sure it's clear that people can and should show up"
" during that time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:13
msgid ""
"Email the participants a week in advance and the day before to remind "
"them to install the needed software before the workshops."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:14
msgid ""
"If possible, recruit  helpers who use Linux, Mac, and Windows operating "
"systems."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:15
msgid ""
"If you/helpers/instructors have time, test the install instructions on a "
"fresh user account on your computer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:16
msgid ""
"If you anticipate issues (or want to be extra prepared), have some of the"
" emergency options listed below ready to go."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:17
msgid ""
"If you're teaching for an organization where participants are bringing "
"work laptops where they don't have administrative access (common in "
"government organizations) -- ask about it.  Try to plan ahead either with"
" their central IT organization or with the \"emergency exits\" listed "
"below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:18
msgid ""
"Will you have decent Wi-Fi?  A bunch of people installing software at "
"once can kill a poor internet connection.  If this is the case, prep a "
"few flash drives with the relevant installers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:20
msgid "On the day of:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:22
msgid "Refer to our Wiki page with common problems"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:23
msgid ""
"If someone has come in early and the software still can't be installed by"
" the time the workshop starts, try one of the \"emergency exits\" below "
"or keep working with them one-on-one until they're able to start."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:24
msgid ""
"If someone comes in late or is having such trouble with installation that"
" they can't start, have them watch (and maybe work with a neighbor) until"
" the first coffee break, when you can keep working on installation "
"issues."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:26
msgid "\"Emergency Exits\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:28
msgid ""
"If there's absolutely no way that you'll be able to install the software "
"locally on someone's computer, consider using the following:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:30
msgid "The \"cloud\" variants of RStudio or Jupyter."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:31
msgid ""
"Microsoft Azure gives you a cloud based Jupyter notebook with many "
"languages and platforms installed.  It also includes a shell terminal "
"with git."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:32
msgid ""
"If your institution's library does laptop rentals, rent 1-2 laptops and "
"set them up with the software before the workshop and keep them on hand "
"as loaners during the workshop."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:34
msgid "Talking About the Code of Conduct"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:36
msgid ""
"The Carpentries Code of Conduct is a key tool for fostering and upholding"
" an inclusive, respectful learning environment.  But for people who are "
"new to the idea of a Code of Conduct, it can be a little awkward to talk "
"about.  Here's a sample of how you might introduce the Code of Conduct --"
" please don't use this verbatim, but adapt it to your own audience and "
"style of introduction:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:38
msgid ""
"The Carpentries is a community-led project. We value the involvement of "
"everyone in the community. We are committed to creating a friendly and "
"respectful place for learning, teaching and contributing. All "
"participants in our events and communications are expected to show "
"respect and courtesy to others."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:40
msgid "What kinds of behaviors are expected?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:42
msgid ""
"All interactions should be professional regardless of platform: either "
"online or in-person. In order to foster a positive and professional "
"learning environment we encourage the following kinds of behaviours in "
"all Carpentries events and platforms:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:44
msgid "Use welcoming and inclusive language"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:45
msgid "Be respectful of different viewpoints and experiences"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:46
msgid "Gracefully accept constructive criticism"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:47
msgid "Focus on what is best for the community"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:48
msgid "Show courtesy and respect towards other community members"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:50
msgid ""
"Examples of unacceptable behavior by participants at any Carpentries "
"event/platform can be found in the Code of Conduct. We Instructors take "
"the Code of Conduct very seriously, and we have a process for dealing "
"with violations and complaints. Read the Reporting Guidelines section for"
" the  details on how to handle Code of Conduct violations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:52
msgid "Using Exercises"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:54
msgid ""
"When teaching a lesson, it's a very good idea to go through the lesson in"
" advance and choose which exercises you want participants to try."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:56
msgid ""
"Once you've selected exercises, there are several ways to actually "
"display them to the participants during the workshop.  Any of these "
"options may be the best choice depending on the tool you're using or the "
"kind of exercises you want to use."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:58
msgid "From the lesson website (zoomed in)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:59
msgid ""
"This is the least effort, but requires having the right lesson page open "
"+ finding the right exercise"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:60
msgid "Make slides"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:61
msgid "More effort, but easy to flip forward to the next one"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:62
msgid "Have a document of some kind with all the exercises in it"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:63
msgid "More effort, but exercises are all in one place."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:64
msgid "Put exercises in the etherpad"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:65
msgid "If you do this in advance, pretty low-effort."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:66
msgid ""
"Can also use this with any of the other strategies so people can find the"
" exercise in two places."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:67
msgid "Online tool, like Socrative"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:68
msgid ""
"Requires time to set up, but is great for multiple choice and T/F "
"questions and promotes participation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:70
msgid ""
"In all of these examples, you'll have to switch from the tool you're "
"using for live coding to however you're showing the exercises.  For "
"something like R or Python, one way to reduce the amount of switching is "
"to put all the exercises in an R script / Python notebook and have that "
"open alongside your main working script/notebook so that it's relatively "
"easy to switch back and forth."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:72
msgid "General Tips"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:74
msgid "Introductions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:76
msgid ""
"The introduction is one of the most important pieces of the workshop!  It"
" sets the tone for the day.  See the instructor training material for "
"some suggestions of how to build a good workshop introduction."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:78
msgid "Accessibility Check-In"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:80
msgid "Before you start, review our  accessibility checkist.."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:82
msgid ""
"Set up your computer and go to the back of the room.  Is your font big "
"enough?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:84
msgid ""
"If your room has a mic, use it, and have a helper stand in the back of "
"the room as you start to confirm that you can be heard."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:94
msgid "Varying Skill Level"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:96
msgid ""
"Carpentries workshops frequently include many people with widely varying "
"skills and experiences.  See the end of the Carpentries Instructor "
"Training on Carpentries teaching practices for some strategies to deal "
"with a diverse classroom."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:98
msgid "Preparing to Teach"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:100
msgid ""
"It can be daunting to look at a Carpentries lesson and figure out just "
"exactly how you're going to teach it.  Here are some suggestions for "
"tackling a new lesson that you've never taught before:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:102
msgid "Read through the Instructor Guide for the Lesson"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:104
msgid ""
"Most Carpentries lessons include a guide for instructors. These are great"
" for novices preparing to teach a lesson for the first time. As an "
"example, see the instructor notes for the Software Carpentry Unix Shell "
"lesson. Find instructor notes for other lessons through the Extras menu "
"on each lesson's home page."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:106
msgid "Pick Exercises"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:108
msgid ""
"Most of the lessons have more exercises than you will want to use.  Go "
"through the lesson and pick the ones that you think will be most helpful "
"for your audience.  If you anticipate mostly novices, look for easier or "
"more scaffolded exercises.  For a more advanced audience, a more general "
"exercise might be better.  If you'll have both, have an option for each!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:110
msgid ""
"You won't want to use all the exercises, but make sure that in this "
"process, you commit to actually doing exercises.  Exercises are time-"
"consuming and it can be tempting (in the moment) to talk instead of "
"taking the time to do an exercise.  However, doing exercises is a huge "
"part of the hands-on Carpentries model and also gives people a chance to "
"chat with their neighbors, so it should be prioritized."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:112
msgid "Speaking of priorities..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:114
msgid "Prioritize"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:116
msgid ""
"All of The Carpentries lessons have more material than you can easily "
"cover in the time alloted, especially with a novice group.  The Data "
"Carpentry materials are closer to realistic workshop time estimates, but "
"can still run slowly depending on the group."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:118
msgid ""
"So no matter what, go through the lesson in advance and decide what is "
"most important to cover and what you would feel okay skipping (either "
"skipping outright, or dropping it if you don't have time)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:120
msgid ""
"As an example: the shell lesson has 7 sections -- the first three are "
"about basic file system navigation and file operations and the last four "
"are about ways to use simple shell tools in more powerful ways.  Often a "
"workshop will cover the first three and then three out of the last four."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:122
msgid "Practice"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:124
msgid ""
"At the very least, do a dry run of all the commands you will be running /"
" code you'll be writing so that you know they work on your computer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:125
msgid ""
"Hook your computer up to a projector and figure out how you're going to "
"manage your screen real estate, especially if everything is magnified."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:126
msgid ""
"Rstudio: Rstudio can be particularly challenging because of all the "
"panes.  Reducing the size of the two right panes is usually needed to "
"have enough space in the script/console panes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:127
msgid ""
"Jupyter notebooks: you can toggle the headers/toolbar off so that you "
"have more scripting space"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:128
msgid ""
"If you have the time, doing a full run-through where you actually "
"practice what you're going to say can be extremely valuable.  Words are "
"hard when you're also trying to type and manage a classroom, so having "
"said them once in practice gives you one less new thing to think about."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:130
msgid "Join a community discussion"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/hosts_instructors/instructor_tips.md:132
msgid ""
"Joining a community discussion before your workshop is a great way to "
"ask/resolve your questions about your coming workshop and also learn from"
" the experience of other instructors!"
msgstr ""

